                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> A @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained], or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Unconscious] creature is within the ghoul's reach</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The ghoul whispers dark thoughts and vile cravings into the creature's ears. The creature must save against the forbidden cravings curse.</p>\n<p><strong>Forbidden Cravings</strong> (curse) A creature can still eat and drink while sickened by this curse</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[will|dc:26|traits:curse]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> carrier with no ill effects (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @Damage[2d6[void]] damage and the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} until it consumes raw meat (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> as stage 2</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> as stage 2 unless the target has consumed raw meat in the past 24 hours, then it takes @Damage[4d6[void]] damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} until it consumes raw meat;</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> if the creature has eaten raw meat in the past 24 hours, it dies and rises as a ghoul, if not, it returns to stage 4</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "ORC",
                    "remaster": true,
                    "title": "Pathfinder Monster Core"
                },
